    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>THE BRADYS AND THE GUN LOBBY</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I propose that anyone who wishes to possess a firearm should become an automatic candidate for conscription, should such a need arise. This policy would be consistent with the intent of the Second Amendment, which was to have civilians carry arms so that a larger army could be raised at relatively short notice. Carrying arms might best be regarded as a privilege that comes with a cost. MAHESH CHITRAO</p>
        <p>Brooklyn</p>
